            "content": "<style type=\"text/css\"> @import url(\"https://www.bbassets.com/static/froala_style_v2.min.css\"); </style>\n        <div style=\"font-family: 'ProximaNova-Regular';font-size:13px;line-height: 18px;color:8f8f8f;\">\n            <p>Banana Robusta is one of the most widely consumed banana varieties. These bananas are known for their distinctive, sweet flavours and creamy texture. They have a vibrant yellow skin when ripe, which encases a high-starch content flesh, making them ideal for cooking and baking. Banana Robusta is also a key ingredient in smoothies, desserts, and even savoury dishes. Moreover, they have a longer shelf life compared to other varieties. The Robusta is not just a tasty snack, but also a versatile ingredient that enhances the flavours of many recipes. The Banana Robusta is appreciated for its size, typically larger than other banana species, making it a substantial snack. The variety is also frequently used in for items such as banana chips, banana bread, and baby food due to its consistent texture and sweetness.</p><p><br></p><p>Don't forget to check out our delicious fruit recipe - <a href=\"https://www.bigbasket.com/cookbook/recipes/1781/banana-smoothie/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.bigbasket.com/cookbook/recipes/1781/banana-smoothie/ </a></p>\n        </div>",
